.TH CCDL2 1NEMO "9 January 2022"

.SH "NAME"
ccdl2 \- find the Lagrangian points in a 2D potential

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBccdl2\fP [parameter=value]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

For a 2D potential (or any image) on a grid, this program will
list the local minima, maxima and saddle points. In rotating potentials
these are the L1, L2, L3, L4 and L5 lagrangian points.
.PP
For a barred galaxy (see e.g. Sellwood & Wilkinson, 1993) L3 (center),
L4 and L5 (along minor axis) are stable,
whereas L1,L2 (along major axis) are unstable.
.PP
For a two-body system L4,L5 are stable (as long as the mass ratio > 24), and L1,L2,L3
are all unstable!

